{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PpyWpfbthxMzy8eRcxiqce","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: \"PRD-224.1\"\n3\ttitle: \"Public check function: validate_review_branches\"\n4\tkind: task\n5\tstatus: review\n6\tpriority: high\n7\teffort: xs\n8\tcapability: simple\n9\tparent: \"[[PRD-224-harness-invariants-honest-state]]\"\n10\tdepends_on: []\n11\tblocks:\n12\t  - \"[[PRD-224.2-ensure-worktree-stale-guard]]\"\n13\t  - \"[[PRD-224.4-cleanup-subcommand]]\"\n14\t  - \"[[PRD-224.7-reconcile-status]]\"\n15\timpacts:\n16\t  - src/darkfactory/checks.py\n17\t  - src/darkfactory/cli.py\n18\t  - tests/test_checks.py\n19\tworkflow: null\n20\ttarget_version: null\n21\tcreated: 2026-04-08\n22\tupdated: '2026-04-08'\n23\ttags:\n24\t  - harness\n25\t  - invariants\n26\t  - hygiene\n27\t---\n28\t\n29\t# Public check function: validate_review_branches\n30\t\n31\t## Summary\n32\t\n33\tExtract a public check function `darkfactory.checks.validate_review_branches(prds, git_state) -> list[Issue]` that returns a list of \"PRD is in review but its branch is gone from origin\" issues. Wire it into `prd validate` so it surfaces the issues as warnings. Other commands and SystemOperations can call the same function.\n34\t\n35\tThis is a `[primitive]` — a reusable check function, not hard-coded logic.\n36\t\n37\t## Requirements\n38\t\n39\t1. Create a new module `src/darkfactory/checks.py` with a `validate_review_branches` function.\n40\t2. The function takes injected dependencies (`prds` dict, `git_state` adapter) so it's testable without a real repo.\n41\t3. The function returns a list of `Issue` objects (or dataclass) describing each PRD that is in `review` status but whose branch is gone from origin.\n42\t4. Wire the function into the existing `prd validate` command so it runs as part of validation and surfaces issues as warnings (not errors — the PRD file itself is still valid).\n43\t5. Unit tests covering: no issues found, one stale PRD, multiple stale PRDs, PRD in review with branch still present.\n44\t\n45\t## Technical Approach\n46\t\n47\t### `src/darkfactory/checks.py`\n48\t\n49\t```python\n50\t@dataclass\n51\tclass Issue:\n52\t    prd_id: str\n53\t    message: str\n54\t    severity: str  # \"warning\" | \"error\"\n55\t\n56\tdef validate_review_branches(\n57\t    prds: dict[str, PRDMeta],\n58\t    git_state: GitStateAdapter,\n59\t) -> list[Issue]:\n60\t    \"\"\"Return issues for PRDs in 'review' whose branch is gone from origin.\"\"\"\n61\t    issues = []\n62\t    for prd_id, meta in prds.items():\n63\t        if meta.status != \"review\":\n64\t            continue\n65\t        branch = f\"prd/{prd_id}-{meta.slug}\"\n66\t        if not git_state.remote_branch_exists(branch):\n67\t            issues.append(Issue(\n68\t                prd_id=prd_id,\n69\t                message=f\"{prd_id} is in 'review' but branch '{branch}' is gone from origin\",\n70\t                severity=\"warning\",\n71\t            ))\n72\t    return issues\n73\t```\n74\t\n75\t### `src/darkfactory/cli.py`\n76\t\n77\tIn `cmd_validate`, after existing validation logic:\n78\t\n79\t```python\n80\tfrom darkfactory.checks import validate_review_branches\n81\tissues = validate_review_branches(prds, git_state)\n82\tfor issue in issues:\n83\t    console.print(f\"[yellow]WARNING:[/yellow] {issue.message}\")\n84\t```\n85\t\n86\t### `tests/test_checks.py`\n87\t\n88\tTest with mock `prds` dict and mock `git_state` adapter. Cover:\n89\t- Empty prds dict -> no issues\n90\t- PRD in review, branch exists -> no issues\n91\t- PRD in review, branch gone -> one issue\n92\t- Multiple PRDs in review, mixed -> correct subset\n93\t\n94\t## Acceptance Criteria\n95\t\n96\t- [ ] AC-1: `darkfactory.checks.validate_review_branches` exists and is importable.\n97\t- [ ] AC-2: The function returns an empty list when all review-status PRDs have their branches present on origin.\n98\t- [ ] AC-3: The function returns an Issue for each PRD in `review` whose branch is gone from origin.\n99\t- [ ] AC-4: `prd validate` calls the function and prints warnings for any issues found.\n100\t- [ ] AC-5: Unit tests pass for all described scenarios.\n101\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fdfb98d4-32e9-4fa7-a46c-bf4d30fd4fa2","uuid":"e38d9c08-9b0e-4feb-b88c-3ca2b81edd53","timestamp":"2026-04-09T02:18:00.936Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-549-builtins-package-split/prds/PRD-224.1-validate-review-branches.md","content":"---\nid: \"PRD-224.1\"\ntitle: \"Public check function: validate_review_branches\"\nkind: task\nstatus: review\npriority: high\neffort: xs\ncapability: simple\nparent: \"[[PRD-224-harness-invariants-honest-state]]\"\ndepends_on: []\nblocks:\n  - \"[[PRD-224.2-ensure-worktree-stale-guard]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-224.4-cleanup-subcommand]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-224.7-reconcile-status]]\"\nimpacts:\n  - src/darkfactory/checks.py\n  - src/darkfactory/cli.py\n  - tests/test_checks.py\nworkflow: null\ntarget_version: null\ncreated: 2026-04-08\nupdated: '2026-04-08'\ntags:\n  - harness\n  - invariants\n  - hygiene\n---\n\n# Public check function: validate_review_branches\n\n## Summary\n\nExtract a public check function `darkfactory.checks.validate_review_branches(prds, git_state) -> list[Issue]` that returns a list of \"PRD is in review but its branch is gone from origin\" issues. Wire it into `prd validate` so it surfaces the issues as warnings. Other commands and SystemOperations can call the same function.\n\nThis is a `[primitive]` — a reusable check function, not hard-coded logic.\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. Create a new module `src/darkfactory/checks.py` with a `validate_review_branches` function.\n2. The function takes injected dependencies (`prds` dict, `git_state` adapter) so it's testable without a real repo.\n3. The function returns a list of `Issue` objects (or dataclass) describing each PRD that is in `review` status but whose branch is gone from origin.\n4. Wire the function into the existing `prd validate` command so it runs as part of validation and surfaces issues as warnings (not errors — the PRD file itself is still valid).\n5. Unit tests covering: no issues found, one stale PRD, multiple stale PRDs, PRD in review with branch still present.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### `src/darkfactory/checks.py`\n\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass Issue:\n    prd_id: str\n    message: str\n    severity: str  # \"warning\" | \"error\"\n\ndef validate_review_branches(\n    prds: dict[str, PRDMeta],\n    git_state: GitStateAdapter,\n) -> list[Issue]:\n    \"\"\"Return issues for PRDs in 'review' whose branch is gone from origin.\"\"\"\n    issues = []\n    for prd_id, meta in prds.items():\n        if meta.status != \"review\":\n            continue\n        branch = f\"prd/{prd_id}-{meta.slug}\"\n        if not git_state.remote_branch_exists(branch):\n            issues.append(Issue(\n                prd_id=prd_id,\n                message=f\"{prd_id} is in 'review' but branch '{branch}' is gone from origin\",\n                severity=\"warning\",\n            ))\n    return issues\n```\n\n### `src/darkfactory/cli.py`\n\nIn `cmd_validate`, after existing validation logic:\n\n```python\nfrom darkfactory.checks import validate_review_branches\nissues = validate_review_branches(prds, git_state)\nfor issue in issues:\n    console.print(f\"[yellow]WARNING:[/yellow] {issue.message}\")\n```\n\n### `tests/test_checks.py`\n\nTest with mock `prds` dict and mock `git_state` adapter. Cover:\n- Empty prds dict -> no issues\n- PRD in review, branch exists -> no issues\n- PRD in review, branch gone -> one issue\n- Multiple PRDs in review, mixed -> correct subset\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `darkfactory.checks.validate_review_branches` exists and is importable.\n- [ ] AC-2: The function returns an empty list when all review-status PRDs have their branches present on origin.\n- [ ] AC-3: The function returns an Issue for each PRD in `review` whose branch is gone from origin.\n- [ ] AC-4: `prd validate` calls the function and prints warnings for any issues found.\n- [ ] AC-5: Unit tests pass for all described scenarios.\n","numLines":101,"startLine":1,"totalLines":101}}}
