{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01YJddxn3BqXry78Tu4PTWhX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01GM32DTqWDzqqNgAtkuDfX6","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-549-builtins-package-split/prds/PRD-549.3-move-ensure-worktree.md","content":"---\nid: \"PRD-549.3\"\ntitle: \"Move ensure_worktree to its own submodule with colocated tests\"\nkind: task\nstatus: ready\npriority: medium\neffort: s\ncapability: simple\nparent: \"[[PRD-549-builtins-package-split]]\"\ndepends_on:\n  - \"[[PRD-549.1-pytest-config-wheel-conftest]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-549.2-scaffold-builtins-package]]\"\nblocks:\n  - \"[[PRD-549.12-final-cleanup]]\"\nimpacts:\n  - src/darkfactory/builtins/ensure_worktree.py\n  - src/darkfactory/builtins/ensure_worktree_test.py\n  - src/darkfactory/builtins/__init__.py\nworkflow: null\ntarget_version: null\ncreated: 2026-04-08\nupdated: 2026-04-08\ntags:\n  - refactor\n  - tests\n  - organization\n---\n\n# Move ensure_worktree to its own submodule with colocated tests\n\n## Summary\n\nExtract the `ensure_worktree` builtin function and its exclusively-used private helpers (`_worktree_target`, `_branch_exists_local`, `_branch_exists_remote`) from `builtins/__init__.py` into `src/darkfactory/builtins/ensure_worktree.py`. Create a colocated `ensure_worktree_test.py` with unit tests covering the function's branches.\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. Create `src/darkfactory/builtins/ensure_worktree.py` containing the `ensure_worktree` function decorated with `@builtin(\"ensure_worktree\")`, plus its private helpers: `_worktree_target`, `_branch_exists_local`, `_branch_exists_remote`.\n2. Create `src/darkfactory/builtins/ensure_worktree_test.py` with unit tests covering: dry-run path, resume existing worktree, branch-exists error, successful creation, lock acquisition and timeout.\n3. Remove `ensure_worktree` and its private helpers from `builtins/__init__.py`.\n4. Add `from darkfactory.builtins import ensure_worktree as ensure_worktree_mod` (or equivalent) import in `__init__.py` to trigger registration.\n5. All existing tests pass. `just test`, `just lint`, `just typecheck`, `just format-check` all clean.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### `src/darkfactory/builtins/ensure_worktree.py`\n\n```python\nfrom __future__ import annotations\nimport logging\nimport subprocess\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom filelock import FileLock, Timeout\nfrom darkfactory.builtins._registry import builtin\nfrom darkfactory.workflow import ExecutionContext\n\n_log = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\ndef _worktree_target(ctx: ExecutionContext) -> Path: ...\ndef _branch_exists_local(repo_root: Path, branch: str) -> bool: ...\ndef _branch_exists_remote(repo_root: Path, branch: str) -> bool: ...\n\n@builtin(\"ensure_worktree\")\ndef ensure_worktree(ctx: ExecutionContext) -> None: ...\n```\n\n### `src/darkfactory/builtins/ensure_worktree_test.py`\n\nUnit tests using mocked subprocess and mocked `ExecutionContext`:\n- Dry-run sets `ctx.worktree_path` and `ctx.cwd` without subprocess calls\n- Existing worktree path resumes without creating a new one\n- Branch exists locally/remotely raises `RuntimeError`\n- Successful creation calls `git worktree add`\n- Lock timeout raises with clear message\n\n### `src/darkfactory/builtins/__init__.py`\n\nAdd import: `from darkfactory.builtins import ensure_worktree as _ensure_worktree_mod`\nKeep re-export: `from darkfactory.builtins.ensure_worktree import ensure_worktree`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `src/darkfactory/builtins/ensure_worktree.py` contains the `ensure_worktree` function and its private helpers.\n- [ ] AC-2: `ensure_worktree_test.py` covers dry-run, resume, branch-exists error, creation, and lock paths.\n- [ ] AC-3: `ensure_worktree` is no longer defined in `builtins/__init__.py`.\n- [ ] AC-4: `from darkfactory.builtins import ensure_worktree` still works.\n- [ ] AC-5: All tests pass. `just test`, `just lint`, `just typecheck`, `just format-check` all clean.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":276,"cache_read_input_tokens":44614,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":276},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fdfb98d4-32e9-4fa7-a46c-bf4d30fd4fa2","uuid":"7c232082-d79a-458a-8694-59b601ec58b1"}
