anch_exists_local`, `_branch_exists_remote`.\n2. Create `src/darkfactory/builtins/ensure_worktree_test.py` with unit tests covering: dry-run path, resume existing worktree, branch-exists error, successful creation, lock acquisition and timeout.\n3. Remove `ensure_worktree` and its private helpers from `builtins/__init__.py`.\n4. Add `from darkfactory.builtins import ensure_worktree as ensure_worktree_mod` (or equivalent) import in `__init__.py` to trigger registration.\n5. All existing tests pass. `just test`, `just lint`, `just typecheck`, `just format-check` all clean.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### `src/darkfactory/builtins/ensure_worktree.py`\n\n```python\nfrom __future__ import annotations\nimport logging\nimport subprocess\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom filelock import FileLock, Timeout\nfrom darkfactory.builtins._registry import builtin\nfrom darkfactory.workflow import ExecutionContext\n\n_log = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\ndef _worktree_target(ctx: ExecutionContext) -> Path: ...\ndef _branch_exists_local(repo_root: Path, branch: str) -> bool: ...\ndef _branch_exists_remote(repo_root: Path, branch: str) -> bool: ...\n\n@builtin(\"ensure_worktree\")\ndef ensure_worktree(ctx: ExecutionContext) -> None: ...\n```\n\n### `src/darkfactory/builtins/ensure_worktree_test.py`\n\nUnit tests using mocked subprocess and mocked `ExecutionContext`:\n- Dry-run sets `ctx.worktree_path` and `ctx.cwd` without subprocess calls\n- Existing worktree path resumes without creating a new one\n- Branch exists locally/remotely raises `RuntimeError`\n- Successful creation calls `git worktree add`\n- Lock timeout raises with clear message\n\n### `src/darkfactory/builtins/__init__.py`\n\nAdd import: `from darkfactory.builtins import ensure_worktree as _ensure_worktree_mod`\nKeep re-export: `from darkfactory.builtins.ensure_worktree import ensure_worktree`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `src/darkfactory/builtins/ensure_worktree.py` contains the `ensure_worktree` function and